claim.claim-text:
1. A method of forming bitlines and bitline contacts for dynamic memory cell arrays, the method which comprises: 
providing a dynamic memory cell array including a planarized surface, a plurality of juxtaposed memory cells on a semiconductor substrate, each having a storage capacitor and a transistor with a source, a drain, and a gate portion; 
insulating the memory cells from each other with an insulating material; 
depositing a first dielectric layer on the planarized surface of the memory cell array, the first dielectric layer having a surface; 
subsequently forming a contact hole in the first dielectric layer penetrating through the first dielectric layer; 
filling the contact hole with a first conductive material to form a bitline contact; 
electrically contacting the first conductive material with one of the source and drain portions of the transistor; 
depositing a second dielectric layer on the surface of the first dielectric layer; and 
thereafter defining a wiring structure of a second conductive material having a higher conductivity than the first conductive material in the second dielectric layer to form the bitline.

8. The method according to claim 1, wherein the step of defining a wiring structure of a second conductive material in the second dielectric layer further comprises: , 
applying a photoresist material on the surface of the second dielectric layer; 
lithographically defining the wiring structures in the photoresist material to expose portions of the second dielectric layer; 
selectively etching the second dielectric layer in the exposed portions; and 
filling the etched portions with the second conductive material.

9. A dynamic memory cell array, comprising: 
a substrate; 
a plurality of memory cells juxtaposed on said semiconductor substrate (19), each of said memory cells including a storage capacitor and a transistor having a source, a drain (10), and a gate portion (18); 
a planarized surface over the memory cells; 
insulating material insulating said memory cells from each other; 
a bitline having a bitline contact electrically contacting one of said source and drain portion of at least one of said memory cells via at least one bitline contact, said bitline contact including a first dielectric layer having a surface and being deposited on said planarized surface, said first dielectric layer having a contact hole formed therein and penetrating therethrough; 
said bitline contact being a first conductive material filling said contact hole and electrically contacting said one of said source and drain portion of said at least one of said memory cells, so as to form said bitline contact; 
a second dielectric layer disposed on said surface of said first dielectric layer; and 
said bitline including a wiring structure of a second conductive material having a higher conductivity than said second dielectric layer.
